com.ekito.simpleKML.model

Class Model

  • java.lang.Object
    • com.ekito.simpleKML.model.Object
      • com.ekito.simpleKML.model.Geometry
        • com.ekito.simpleKML.model.Model

  • public class Model
extends Geometry
    A 3D object described in a COLLADA file (referenced in the Link tag). COLLADA files have a .dae file extension. Models are created in their own coordinate space and then located, positioned, and scaled in Google Earth. See the "Topics in KML" page on Models for more detail. Google Earth supports the COLLADA common profile, with the following exceptions:
    • Google Earth supports only triangles and lines as primitive types. The maximum number of triangles allowed is 21845.
    • Google Earth does not support animation or skinning.
    • Google Earth does not support external geometry references.
